---
import {
	CodeBlock,
	Heading,
	Link,
	ListItem,
	ScrollContainer,
	Text,
	Title,
	QuoteBlock,
	UnorderedList,
	colors,
	spacing,
	experimentalTypeScale,
} from "@nuttyverse/blocks";
import UniversalLayout from "../layouts/UniversalLayout.astro";
---

<UniversalLayout title="Nuttyverse">
	<div
		style={{
			display: "flex",
			flexDirection: "column",
			height: "100%",
			gap: spacing[2],
		}}
	>
		<Title>‚òô Colophon ‚ùß</Title>

		<ScrollContainer style={{ flex: 1 }} client:only="react">
			<div
				style={{ width: "100%", paddingLeft: "1rem", paddingRight: "1rem" }}
			>
				<Text dropCap
					>The Nuttyverse is a personal publishing platform for my creative
					and recreational pursuits, imbued with ‚ôå-energy and a pinch of
					whimsical delusion. It has been slowly expanding since July 2023.</Text
				>
			</div>
			<Heading type="h2">Ethos</Heading>
			<div
				style={{ width: "100%", paddingLeft: "1rem", paddingRight: "1rem" }}
			>
				<Text
					>Like many others in the <Link
						href="https://neocities.org/"
						newTab>Neocities</Link
					> community, I have become discontent with how corporatized the Internet
					has become. I yearn for the early days of the web that felt more personal
					and less commercialized. So this is my contribution to bringing back
					that lost individual creativity of the web.</Text
				>
				<Text
					>This website will be under construction indefinitely, most
					definitely. You see, I have perfectionistic tendencies, and so I
					often find myself absorbed in the small details that don't
					matter. But please, do not misunderstand: that is exactly the
					point.</Text
				>
				<Text
					>The minutiae brings me joy, and I am just going to play with it.
					As the physicist Richard Feynman put it, <Link
						href="https://www.asc.ohio-state.edu/kilcup.1/262/feynman.html"
						newTab
						>"There's no importance whatsoever. I'm just doing it for the
						fun of it."</Link
					> I wish to pursue webmastery with that same kind of autotelic attitude.</Text
				>
			</div>
			<Heading type="h2">Technology</Heading>
			<div
				style={{ width: "100%", paddingLeft: "1rem", paddingRight: "1rem" }}
			>
				<Text
					>The Nuttyverse is (over-)engineered as a set of polyglot
					Œº-services running in a swarm of Docker containers deployed on a
					bare-metal NixOS server -- with the exception of this static
					website that you are currently navigating, which is deployed on
					Neocities.</Text
				>
				<Text
					>If you are interested in taking a peek into the internals, the
					code happens to be open-sourced and published in a <Link
						href="https://code.nuttyver.se/observable/nuttyverse"
						newTab>git monorepo</Link
					>. But don't let me find you blatantly copying it... or else!
				</Text>
			</div>
			<CodeBlock
				client:visible="react"
				language="bash"
				code={`
git clone https://code.nuttyver.se/observable/nuttyverse.git
cd nuttyverse && cat curse.txt
			`.trim()}
			/>
			<div
				style={{ width: "100%", paddingLeft: "1rem", paddingRight: "1rem" }}
			>
				<QuoteBlock
					citation="https://code.nuttyver.se/observable/nuttyverse/src/branch/main/curse.txt"
					style={{ marginTop: "1.2rem", marginBottom: "1.2rem" }}
				>
					<pre
						style={{
							fontFamily: "PragmataPro Fraktur",
							fontSize: experimentalTypeScale.smol,
							color: colors.gray.solid["12"],
						}}>
"Please peruse & muse upon the code,
but best not fork it," Nutty implores,
lest, cursed, it might just explode,
"For my style is mine & yours is yours."</pre>
				</QuoteBlock>

				<Text
					>I read on Wikipedia that colophons would sometimes contain <Link
						href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_curse"
						newTab>book curses</Link
					> in early printed publications. I found that idea to be quite amusing,
					so I thought to irreverently place one in mine. <Link
						href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v4YnyVdMjG4"
						newTab>Muahahaha</Link
					>, it's such an evil thing to do! It feels delightfully roguish.</Text
				>
			</div>
			<Heading type="h2">Typography</Heading>
			<div
				style={{ width: "100%", paddingLeft: "1rem", paddingRight: "1rem" }}
			>
				<Text>
					<UnorderedList>
						<ListItem
							>Words are set in <span
								style={{
									fontFamily: "Nure",
									fontWeight: "bold",
								}}>Nure</span
							> and <span
								style={{
									fontFamily: "PragmataPro Fraktur",
									fontWeight: "bold",
								}}>PragmataPro Fraktur</span
							>.</ListItem
						>
						<ListItem
							>Code is set in <span
								style={{
									fontFamily: "PragmataPro Liga",
									fontWeight: "bold",
								}}>PragmataPro Liga</span
							>.</ListItem
						>
						<ListItem
							>Icons are set with
							<span
								style={{
									fontFamily: "'FSD Emoji'",
									fontWeight: "bold",
									fontVariantLigatures: "none",
								}}>FSD Emoji üòÄ</span
							> and
							<span
								style={{
									fontFamily: "'Font Awesome 6 Pro'",
									fontWeight: "bold",
									fontVariantLigatures: "none",
								}}>Font Awesome Ôä¥</span
							>
							.</ListItem
						>
					</UnorderedList>
				</Text>
			</div>
		</ScrollContainer>
	</div>
</UniversalLayout>
